    <etym xml:lang="ru">Воспринято из языков черкесской группы; ср. <mentioned xml:lang=""
                ><lang/><w>čʼibžʼije</w><gloss><q>türkischer Pfeffer</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Mészaros"/><biblScope>286</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>šəbžij</w><gloss><q>стручковый
            перец</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                ><w>šəps</w><gloss><q>горчица</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Отсюда идут также
            <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/><w>čəbəǯə</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="krc-x-karachay"><lang/><w>čəbžə</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"
                ><lang/><w>šibəz</w><gloss><q>стручковый перец</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ср. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_byrc"/> ‘черный перец’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>88, 105</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">The word was borrowed from Circassian group; cf. <mentioned xml:lang=""
                ><lang/><w>čʼibžʼije</w><gloss><q>türkischer Pfeffer</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Mészaros"/><biblScope>286</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>šəbžij</w><gloss><q>pod
            pepper</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                ><w>šəps</w><gloss><q>mustard</q></gloss></mentioned>, . The following words also
        come from here: <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/><w>čəbəǯə</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-karachay"><lang/><w>čəbžə</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="inh"><lang/><w>šibəz</w><gloss><q>pod pepper</q></gloss></mentioned>. Cf. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_byrc"/> ‘black pepper’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>88, 105</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
